  <author>Adrian Leonard Mociulschi</author>
  <category>Technology</category>
  <category>Robotics</category>

  <tags>Pigmalion, robots, Sophia, Aria, Pigmalion myth and AI, love in the age of algorithms, AI art, humanoid robots</tags>

  <description><![CDATA[
    <strong>Pygmalion Reloaded: How Robots, Art, and Digital Love Are Rewriting Human Destiny</strong><br/>
    <img src="https://adrian-leonard-mociulschi.github.io/assets/img/slug-512.jpg" alt="The New Robots" width="512" height="512" />
  ]]></description>

  <content:encoded><![CDATA[
    <p><strong>This essay explores the cultural continuum from Pigmalion’s myth to AI humanoids,</strong> showing how the ancient dream of animating matter evolves into programmable intimacy. 
       From Galatea and Galax to Sophia and Aria, art and love shift from divine gift and chance to algorithmic design and marketable protocol. The central question remains: what does it mean to love when desire becomes an API and compatibility a matter of code?</p>
    <p>
